T1  - Merging short-and long-run forecasts: An application of seasonal cointegration to monthly electricity sales forecasting
AU  - Engle, R.F.
AU  - Granger, C.W.J.
AU  - Hallman, J.J.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 40
IS  - 1
SP  - 45
EP  - 62
PY  - 1989
DA  - 1989/01/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(89)90029-8
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407689900298
AB  - When forecasts of a series Yt must be made for several horizons, it is a common practice to build different models to forecast different horizons. This paper shows how the information in the several models can be combined in an error-correction framework to yield a single set of forecasts which outperform those from the seperate models. The notions of seasonal integration and cointegration are introduced. The methods are applied to forecasting monthly commercial electricity sales with some success. Also reported are results of some simulation experiments designed to evaluate their effectiveness.
ER  - 

